videos.description: Georgia Tech's P.J. Davis picks up the loose ball after Kentucky QB Stephen Johnson was strip sacked, and returns the ball 41 yards for the touchdown.
videos.headline: Georgia Tech takes early lead off scoop and score

videos.description: Kentucky's Jojo Kemp runs for the 25-yard gain, setting up the Wildcats in the red zone.
videos.headline: Kentucky's Kemp energizes Wildcats with 25-yard run

videos.description: Georgia Tech's KeShun Freeman stops Kentucky's Jojo Kemp on 4th down, preventing the Wildcats from scoring.
videos.headline: Georgia Tech stifles Kentucky on 4th down

videos.description: Georgia Tech's Justin Thomas takes the QB sneak all the way and dives for the pylon on a 21-yard touchdown.
videos.headline: Georgia Tech's Thomas keeps it for the TD

videos.description: Georgia Tech blocks the Kentucky punt and recovers the ball late in the second quarter. After the play, the Yellow Jackets' bench gets into it with some Wildcats players.
videos.headline: Georgia Tech blocks Kentucky's punt, scuffle ensues

videos.description: Georgia Tech head coach Paul Johnson talks about the biggest challenge he is facing as a playcaller in the first half of the TaxSlayer Bowl.
videos.headline: Georgia Tech coach shares biggest challenge of first half

videos.description: Kentucky head coach Mark Stoops shares his reaction to refereeing decisions in the first half and how his team must create big plays on offense.
videos.headline: Kentucky coach Mark Stoops frustrated with officials

videos.description: Kentucky's Nico Firios blocks the Georgia Tech punt and recovers the ball, but Kash Daniel costs the Wildcats yardage with a piling on penalty.
videos.headline: Kentucky blocks Georgia Tech's punt, things get chippy

videos.description: Kentucky's Stephen Johnson throws it to Dorian Baker, who makes the great diving catch for the 20-yard touchdown.
videos.headline: Kentucky gets its first TD in the 4th quarter

videos.description: Georgia Tech's Dedrick Mills looks to be falling to the ground, but he stays on his feet to complete a 27-yard run.
videos.headline: Georgia Tech's Mills won't go down, runs for 27 yards

videos.description: Kentucky's Stephen Johnson escapes the pocket for a 21-yard run and lays out into the end zone to bring the Wildcats within eight points after a successful two-point conversion.
videos.headline: Kentucky stays in the game with diving score

videos.description: Georgia Tech head coach Paul Johnson talks about gutsy playcalling, including going for it on fourth downs, in the Yellow Jackets' victory over Kentucky in the TaxSlayer Bowl.
videos.headline: Georgia Tech coach Paul Johnson discusses gutsy playcalling

videos.description: Georgia Tech hoists the TaxSlayer Bowl trophy, and coach Paul Johnson describes how it feels to end the season with a bowl win.
videos.headline: Georgia Tech lifts the TaxSlayer Bowl Trophy

videos.description: Georgia Tech freshman running back Dedrick Mills has a laugh while describing his 31-carry, 169-yard performance in a 33-18 win over Kentucky.
videos.headline: TaxSlayer Bowl MVP Dedrick Mills talks big rushing day
